."}},"top_positives":["Trades above its 200-day average (+23%).","50-day average above the 200-day (golden cross).","Outpacing the NIFTY 500 by +111pp over 12 months.","1.17\u00d7 of profit came in as operating cash (5-yr median) \u2014 well backed.","Conservatively financed (D/E 0.40\u00d7, interest cover 6.7\u00d7).","Profit up 44% YoY (latest TTM) and accelerating."],"key_risks":["P/E at the 93-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 expensive vs its own history.","Promoter stake falling (-1.66pp YoY)."],"monitor_next":["Next quarterly results (board-meeting date is an MVP-2 placeholder).","Re-rating toward / away from its median P/E (13.2\u00d7).","Relative-strength inflection vs its sector index.","Promoter pledge / institutional-holding changes next quarter."],"caveats":["Cheap multiple may sit on peak/cyclical earnings \u2014 Peak-cycle caution: margins AND valuation both in the top quintile of their own history \u2014 the market may be extrapolating peak earnings.","corporate-action gaps, illiquid names, or a short listing history can distort returns/DMA/RS."],"confidence":"high","disclaimer":"Diagnostics only \u2014 a structured reading of price behaviour, business fundamentals, valuation and ownership for your OWN judgement. This is NOT a buy/sell/hold recommendation.","method":"Each dimension is a transparent points tally of the named signals listed beneath it \u2014 open a dimension to see the exact signals that fired and its rule. Verdict = positive at +2 or more / negative at \u22122 or less for Market, Business and Valuation; \u00b11 for Ownership. A 'positive' valuation means the multiple looks supportive vs the stock's OWN history \u2014 never a buy call."},"data_quality":{"price_asof":"2026-06-29","fundamentals_fetched":"2026-06-20","has_fundamentals":true,"has_shareholding":true,"liquidity_warning":null,"note":"Market data is daily and current; fundamentals & shareholding are as of the last cached Screener fetch (quarterly/annual). Confidence is lowe